reviews.content:
I have been critical of Matthew Broderick Jessica Parker since this film. I mean, he set such high expectations with his dramatic work in 'WarGames' (1983), working opposite of that computer... yawn. He makes this film, and the world treats him like a young, sort-of-chubby Tolstoy. Then, he got married, got fat, and became a 'cameo appearance' guy... waddling his fat, grey-haired self around, trying to smirk like Ferris Bueller. I figured it was for the sequel, because 'Ferris Bueller's Got Fat!' (2006) has a certain ring to it...But, alas, Matthew Broderick Jessica Parker wasn't preparing for a role, he was just over-eating to deal with his feelings of inadequacy from watching his wife cash those 'Sex In The City' (1998-2004) checks. Yeah, she's out cashin' those sweet, sweet HBO checks, and he's at home on the couch, eating expired 'Grandpa Eddy's Sweet, Sweet Choco-Potato-Mayo Cakes' (1993).Alan Ruck was good in this film. Somehow, Ruck ages 27 years in the following 10 years, and appears to be in his 40s in Spin City (1996). For those of you that have seen this film 25 times, but are still somehow unfamiliar with 'Spin City'... watching any 4 episodes of Michael J. Fox's 'Spin City' is a better way to spend 90 minutes than watching this film.Someone should ask Alan Ruck about his time machine.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
